[{"question":"Are you aware of the history?","answer":"Well, I\u0027m aware that he was George Washington\u0027s ruthless chief of staff --","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":39,"aSentId":40},{"question":"Really?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":47,"aSentId":48},{"question":"Do you agree with that?","answer":"I -- Piers, we wouldn\u0027t be doing -- you and I wouldn\u0027t be doing this interview if it wasn\u0027t for both the love of our parents and the education we received and their focus on education.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":59,"aSentId":60},{"question":"Why is that?","answer":"Well, the fact is that we haven\u0027t focused like we need to on our educational system.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"How does she define the opportunity to you?","answer":"Well --","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":96,"aSentId":97},{"question":"At the time?","answer":"Well, first of all, there\u0027s a couple of things, and it\u0027s not -- it\u0027s hard to reduce.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":98,"aSentId":99},{"question":"What was your biggest ever failure?","answer":"Well, I\u0027ve had two.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":111,"aSentId":112},{"question":"Which was the finger?","answer":"My middle finger on my right hand.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":119,"aSentId":120},{"question":"Because it was amputated, right?","answer":"Yes, they had died, different -- at different times.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":121,"aSentId":122},{"question":"What did you learn about yourself?","answer":"Well, from the one incidence in the hospital, never, ever take life for granted; more importantly than that, I wanted to get everything I could out of life, because you never know when it can flip on you.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":127,"aSentId":128},{"question":"What is the idea behind bringing them to a school like this?","answer":"Well, first of all, what I -- we have, with Robert F. Kennedy and the City of Chicago, Robert F. Kennedy Foundation, the City of Chicago, the Nobel Peace Prize winners from around the world.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":150,"aSentId":151},{"question":"What would you say?","answer":"Well, first of all, it\u0027s like everything.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":187,"aSentId":188},{"question":"What would you -- what would you put into the must-do-better box?","answer":"Look, he\u0027d be the first to say that there are -- there are more things to do in the sense of getting the middle class the economic security they need.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":207,"aSentId":208},{"question":"How is he going to win the economic argument against Mitt Romney, who will be chucking the kitchen sink at him and saying, I\u0027m the business guy that can get us out of this?","answer":"Well, first of all, the policies Mitt Romney advocate are the policies that got us into it.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":217,"aSentId":218},{"question":"But has he been frustrated, do you think, that he can\u0027t force the rate of change as much as he\u0027d like to, and what does he blame that on?","answer":"Well, you have to -- I\u0027m not going to speak for him.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":227,"aSentId":228},{"question":"-- this election?","answer":"No, no, Piers, you can\u0027t -- there\u0027s a set of -- there\u0027s not a thing to look at both the individuals, their character, their judgment and their policies.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":241,"aSentId":242},{"question":"You don\u0027t buy that?","answer":"No.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":261,"aSentId":262},{"question":"What does being an American mean to you?","answer":"It means a great -- a great country with great people with great promise.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":271,"aSentId":272},{"question":"What are you going to do about this and what does it say about race in America right now?","answer":"Well, first of all, I was in Inglewood yesterday at a church, because we have to bring the ministers and what goes on in that church outside that church.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":296,"aSentId":297},{"question":"Do you agree with that?","answer":"Yes, it\u0027s totally unacceptable.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":333,"aSentId":334},{"question":"Sean, when you were in school, what was the big dream for you?","answer":"Well, in fact, I had been very interested in being a lawyer.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":383,"aSentId":384},{"question":"What did you get from it?","answer":"Well, first of all, looking out at the kids, I think this is a particular school here that we got to visit, because there is really that diversity where -- you know, so much is said about diversity in the United States and yet we don\u0027t make much use of it.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":397,"aSentId":398},{"question":"And how damaged has that become, do you think?","answer":"Well, looking at this group of kids, I think, was very encouraging.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":403,"aSentId":404},{"question":"What do you think of that?","answer":"I would agree with it.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":412,"aSentId":413},{"question":"Are you relieved that Mitt Romney is the assumed nominee for the Republicans, in the sense that he is, by common consent, the least right wing of the ones that were left in the race?","answer":"You know, I -- I don\u0027t know that I feel there\u0027s enormous productivity in talking about Mitt Romney.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":425,"aSentId":426},{"question":"How\u0027s it doing?","answer":"Right now we\u0027re looking to the ratification of Minister Lamont as prime minister.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":461,"aSentId":462},{"question":"How weird is it to be, as you have been in the last few months, making a movie and simultaneously trying to revive a country like Haiti?","answer":"Well -- yeah.","docId":"120423pmt","qSentId":465,"aSentId":466}]